### 4. Frontend — App.vue Integration


Add auth guard at the top of the main template. The app shows LoginView until authenticated:

```vue
<!-- Inside <template>, wrap existing content: -->
<LoginView v-if="!isAuthenticated" @auth-success="onAuthSuccess" />
<div v-else class="autoforge-app">
  <!-- existing nav-rail + view-main content -->
</div>
```

```typescript
// In <script setup>:
import { useAuth } from '@/composables/useAuth'
import LoginView from './views/LoginView.vue'

const { isAuthenticated, validateStoredToken } = useAuth()

// On mount, check for stored token
onMounted(async () => {
  const valid = await validateStoredToken()
  // If invalid, LoginView will show automatically via isAuthenticated
  if (valid) {
    // existing mount logic
    fetchStatus()
  }
})

function onAuthSuccess() {
  // Trigger existing mount logic
  fetchStatus()
}
```

