### 11. Data Lifecycle

```
[Server Start]
  → load_or_create_jwt_secret() reads/generates secret
  → RbacState::new() opens SQLite, runs migration, seeds data
  → Default admin user (admin/admin) created on first run only

[First Visit]
  → App.vue mounts → validateStoredToken() → no token → LoginView shown
  → User enters admin/admin → POST /api/auth/login → JWT returned
  → JWT stored in localStorage → main app loads

[Subsequent Visits]
  → App.vue mounts → validateStoredToken() → token found → GET /api/auth/me
  → Valid response → main app loads directly

[Token Expiry (24h)]
  → Any API call returns 401 → authFetch clears token → LoginView shown

[Logout]
  → User clicks logout → clear localStorage → LoginView shown
```

### 12. Quality Checklist

- [x] Every backend route is either explicitly public or protected by `auth_middleware`
- [x] Default admin user seeded on first run (admin/admin)
- [x] JWT secret persists across server restarts
- [x] Frontend validates stored token on mount
- [x] 401 responses clear auth state and redirect to login
- [x] All existing composables updated to use `authFetch`
- [x] Login and register forms with error display
- [x] i18n keys for both English and Chinese
- [x] No unhandled error cases
- [x] Explicit data lifecycle (token storage, validation, expiry, logout)
